19#ifdef LDAP_THREAD_DEBUG
20
21/*
22 * libldap_r .c files should include this file after ldap_pvt_thread.h,
23 * with the appropriate LDAP_THREAD*_IMPLEMENTATION macro(s) defined.
24 */
25
26#ifndef _LDAP_PVT_THREAD_H
27#error "ldap_pvt_thread.h" must be included before "ldap_thr_debug.h"
28#endif
29
30/*
31 * Support for thr_debug.c:
32 *
33 * thr_debug.c defines ldap_pvt_thread_* as wrappers around the real
34 * ldap_pvt_thread_* implementation, which this file renames to
35 * ldap_int_thread_*.
36 *
37 * Implementation:
38 *
39 * This file re#defines selected ldap_pvt_thread_* names to
40 * ldap_int_thread_*, which will be used from wrappers in thr_debug.c.
41 * Two ldap_int_*() calls are redirected to call ldap_debug_*(): These
42 * are wrappers around the originals, whose definitions are not renamed.
43 * This file then #includes ldap_pvt_thread.h to declare the renamed
44 * functions/types. If #included from thr_debug.c it finally #undefines
45 * the macros again.
46 *
47 * include/ldap_pvt_thread.h declares the typedefs ldap_pvt_thread*_t as
48 * either wrapper types ldap_debug_thread*_t or their usual definitions
49 * ldap_int_thread*_t, depending on the LDAP_THREAD_DEBUG_WRAP option.
50 * When defining the underlying implementation, this file then redirects
51 * the type names back to the original ldap_int_thread*_t types.
52 * include/ldap_<int,pvt>_thread.h also do some thr_debug magic.
53 *
54 * So,
55 * libldap_r/<not thr_debug.c> thus define ldap_int_thread_*() instead
56 * of ldap_pvt_thread_*().
57 * thr_debug.c defines the ldap_pvt_*() and ldap_debug_*() functions.
58 * In thread.c, ldap_pvt_thread_<initialize/destroy>() will call
59 * ldap_debug_thread_*() instead of ldap_int_thread_*().
60 * In tpool.c, ldap_int_thread_pool_shutdown() has explicit thr_debug.c
61 * support which treats ldap_pvt_thread_pool_destroy() the same way.
62 */
63
64#ifndef LDAP_THREAD_IMPLEMENTATION /* for first part of threads.c */
65#define ldap_int_thread_initialize ldap_debug_thread_initialize
66#define ldap_int_thread_destroy ldap_debug_thread_destroy
67#else /* LDAP_THREAD_IMPLEMENTATION -- for thr_*.c and end of threads.c */
68#undef ldap_int_thread_initialize
69#undef ldap_int_thread_destroy
70#ifdef LDAP_THREAD_DEBUG_WRAP /* see ldap_pvt_thread.h */
71#define ldap_pvt_thread_mutex_t ldap_int_thread_mutex_t
72#define ldap_pvt_thread_cond_t ldap_int_thread_cond_t
73#endif
74#define ldap_pvt_thread_sleep ldap_int_thread_sleep
75#define ldap_pvt_thread_get_concurrency ldap_int_thread_get_concurrency
76#define ldap_pvt_thread_set_concurrency ldap_int_thread_set_concurrency
77#define ldap_pvt_thread_create ldap_int_thread_create
78#define ldap_pvt_thread_exit ldap_int_thread_exit
79#define ldap_pvt_thread_join ldap_int_thread_join
80#define ldap_pvt_thread_kill ldap_int_thread_kill
81#define ldap_pvt_thread_yield ldap_int_thread_yield
82#define ldap_pvt_thread_cond_init ldap_int_thread_cond_init
83#define ldap_pvt_thread_cond_destroy ldap_int_thread_cond_destroy
84#define ldap_pvt_thread_cond_signal ldap_int_thread_cond_signal
85#define ldap_pvt_thread_cond_broadcast ldap_int_thread_cond_broadcast
86#define ldap_pvt_thread_cond_wait ldap_int_thread_cond_wait
87#define ldap_pvt_thread_mutex_init ldap_int_thread_mutex_init
88#define ldap_pvt_thread_mutex_destroy ldap_int_thread_mutex_destroy
89#define ldap_pvt_thread_mutex_lock ldap_int_thread_mutex_lock
90#define ldap_pvt_thread_mutex_trylock ldap_int_thread_mutex_trylock
91#define ldap_pvt_thread_mutex_unlock ldap_int_thread_mutex_unlock
92#define ldap_pvt_thread_self ldap_int_thread_self
93#endif /* LDAP_THREAD_IMPLEMENTATION */
94
95#ifdef LDAP_THREAD_RDWR_IMPLEMENTATION /* rdwr.c, thr_debug.c */
96#ifdef LDAP_THREAD_DEBUG_WRAP /* see ldap_pvt_thread.h */
97#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_t ldap_int_thread_rdwr_t
98#endif
99#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_init ldap_int_thread_rdwr_init
100#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_destroy ldap_int_thread_rdwr_destroy
101#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_rlock ldap_int_thread_rdwr_rlock
102#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_rtrylock ldap_int_thread_rdwr_rtrylock
103#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_runlock ldap_int_thread_rdwr_runlock
104#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_wlock ldap_int_thread_rdwr_wlock
105#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_wtrylock ldap_int_thread_rdwr_wtrylock
106#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_wunlock ldap_int_thread_rdwr_wunlock
107#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_readers ldap_int_thread_rdwr_readers
108#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_writers ldap_int_thread_rdwr_writers
109#define ldap_pvt_thread_rdwr_active ldap_int_thread_rdwr_active
110#endif /* LDAP_THREAD_RDWR_IMPLEMENTATION */
111
112#ifdef LDAP_THREAD_POOL_IMPLEMENTATION /* tpool.c, thr_stub.c, thr_debug.c */
113#ifdef LDAP_THREAD_DEBUG_WRAP /* see ldap_pvt_thread.h */
114#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_t ldap_int_thread_pool_t
115#endif
116#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_init ldap_int_thread_pool_init
117#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_submit ldap_int_thread_pool_submit
118#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_maxthreads ldap_int_thread_pool_maxthreads
119#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_backload ldap_int_thread_pool_backload
120#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_pause ldap_int_thread_pool_pause
121#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_resume ldap_int_thread_pool_resume
122#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_destroy ldap_int_thread_pool_destroy
123#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_getkey ldap_int_thread_pool_getkey
124#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_setkey ldap_int_thread_pool_setkey
125#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_purgekey ldap_int_thread_pool_purgekey
126#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_context ldap_int_thread_pool_context
127#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_context_reset ldap_int_thread_pool_context_reset
128#endif /* LDAP_THREAD_POOL_IMPLEMENTATION */

130#undef _LDAP_PVT_THREAD_H
131#include "ldap_pvt_thread.h"

133#ifdef LDAP_THREAD_POOL_IMPLEMENTATION /* tpool.c */
134/*
135 * tpool.c:ldap_int_thread_pool_shutdown() needs this. Could not
136 * use it for ldap_pvt_thread.h above because of its use of LDAP_P().
137 */
138#undef ldap_pvt_thread_pool_destroy
139#define ldap_pvt_thread_pool_destroy(p,r) ldap_int_thread_pool_destroy(p,r)
140#endif
